      "span_text": "The involution σ onX induces an involution σ * on TX. The subgroup of the mapping class group ofX that commutes with σ * is called relative modular group  . (In the case of a closed and oriented surface,X has two connected components of opposite orientation each of which is isomorphic to X. The relative modular group is then isomorphic to the mapping class group of X.)"
